    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. Validation evidence demonstrates adequate predictive capability for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. RHI agreement within 15% for primary QoI across 4 of 5 operating points. GCI below 3.2% confirms discretization error is controlled. The model is accepted as credible for the stated COU of identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions for a Class II CPB device.",
